utterly /ˈʌtəlɪ/

ADV You use utterly to emphasize that something is very great in extent, degree, or amount. 完全地; 彻底地 [强调] 

例： China is utterly different. 中国完全不一样。 

例： The new laws coming in are utterly ridiculous. 即将实施的新法律荒唐至极。

